comment_data.body:
> if that actually works, send a pr. else this is wontfix

@justinmk It works for me. I can send a PR, but I'm not sure about right way to implement this in an LSP config.
At a glance user has no options than `before_init`, but I'm unsure is it a good idea to use `before_init` in base config - this way user won't be able to use  `before_init` for his own tasks without breaking this functionality. Is there any other/better place for this logic in base config?
